                      </td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                </td>
              </tr>

              <tr>
                <td>
                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td align="left" style="padding-top:20px; font-family: 'Open Sans', Verdana, sans-serif; color: #666666; font-size: 20px;" class="padding-copy iphone-header iphone-fix"><font face="'Open Sans', Verdana, sans-serif">5. Resistance to Change</font></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                </td>
              </tr>

              <tr>
                <td>
                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td align="left" style="font-family: 'Open Sans', Verdana, sans-serif; color: #666666; font-size: 16px;" class="padding-copy iphone-text iphone-fix"><font face="'Open Sans', Verdana, sans-serif">Whether your company is a start-up or has been around for 100 years, innovation can be a frightening thing. But change is real. Don't get stuck in archaic ways of doing things. Embrace a culture of forward thinking. Be open with your staff about changes taking place in your organization, as well.</font></td>
                    </tr>
